California gun-control laws cut flow to Mexico - SFGate "A Hearst Newspapers survey of guns purchased in the United States and funneled to Mexican drug traffickers found that out of 1,600 guns identified by brand name and purchase point in court documents, a mere 70 came from California." all 70 of which: "In the Hearst survey's lone California case, Ayman Nabil Ghaly, a federal agriculture inspector at California-Mexico border posts, was charged last year with purchasing 70 guns, mostly handguns, for resale in Mexico. He bought them at gun stores in the San Diego area from June 2005 to September 2006, mostly one or two at a time."